= process by which humans or objects disappear or are removed from existence;◄ either by (a usually unnatural) death, aggression, hardship, disaster, natural processes, acts of destruction, or direct divine intervention

Notes.Content: A proposal has been made of a root אבד II meaning "to endure, to be permanent" (cf. Jenni, THAT 1:18 | Otzen, TWAT 1:21). It is now accepted, or at least strongly suggested, by Gesenius (18) and KAHAL. See the note in אבד 2.
